						               													<description>In Hero Flix, you take on the role of a movie director. Your task is to complete a production and earn Production Points toward a winning score of 10 points. More complex productions have a higher Production Point value but also take longer to complete.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;While working towards Completing a Production, there are opportunities to increase the value of your production or impact the production of other players. Some examples include:&amp;#10;&amp;#10;&amp;#10;    Joining in their success (joining them as a Co-Producer),&amp;#10;    Lowering the Production Point value (through a Smear Campaign), or&amp;#10;    Preventing them from Completing the Production this turn (via an Injunction).&amp;#10;&amp;#10;&amp;#10;Hero Flix enables you to change the level of interaction by removing some cards from the game. We break these styles into three &amp;ldquo;Budget Levels&amp;rdquo;:&amp;#10;&amp;#10;&amp;#10;     &amp;quot;B Movie&amp;quot; - there is a low chance of influencing another player,&amp;#10;     &amp;quot;Major Motion Picture&amp;quot; - you have some chance for influencing another player, and&amp;#10;     &amp;quot;Summer Blockbuster&amp;quot; - another player production will get influenced unless you are doing it wrong. This is how the game was designed to be played.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;&amp;#10;</description>
